mod_ldap crashes when trying to destroy anonymous shared memory in function
util_ldap_cache_module_kill. Since the cache_file pointer ist NULL. Passing NULL
to apr_file_remove causes the crash.
Adding an if seems to resolve the problem. Here's the code:
        if(st->cache_file != NULL) {
            apr_file_remove(st->cache_file, st->pool);
        }
